Most likely why it did not auto-link
1. Auto-link only runs for calendar_blocks where source is gcal and there is no existing storyId/taskId.
2. It only checks a forward horizon window (now to about 45 days), so out-of-window blocks are skipped.
3. It requires title matching score >= 0.72. If the event title was just CSA and did not include story ref/title tokens, score may be too low.
4. It matches only against open story/task candidates; if the intended story is done/deferred/closed, it can be excluded.
5. Persona mismatch between event block and story/task can prevent a valid candidate match.
6. If inbound sync normalized source differently (not gcal), matcher won’t attempt linking.

